Using wiki markup in previous versions of Confluence, users would edit a table manually to insert cells at the end of each row. This would make the table non-rectangular, as each row may have a different number of cells.  They preferred this vs. a rectangular table that had an abundance of empty cells at the end of each row.
Now, the GUI editor wants to only insert whole rows or whole columns, and merging the cells in any way doesn't get me the look I'm trying for. Is there going to be a way to add a new cell to the end of an existing row, without creating a whole column?

