Storing knowledge is one of the strong points of Confluence. However, often knowledge spreads over external links which are embedded throughout a page. But since there is no control over external content, knowledge might become spotty if the external content happens to vanish.

I'd like to propose an option where external links in a page are automatically detected and its contend archived within Confluence. Of course this would have to be restricted to some degree since mirroring entire sites is no fun for anyone. It does not have to be perfect. Even a shabby and badly formatted .pdf version of the external content (depth == 1) would suffice. Because if important content is missing, I'd rather have a badly formatted copy instead of nothing.

